The paper deals with optimization problems related to inventory management and routing, which are typically studied in the fields of operations research and management science. The use of submodular functions and routing costs suggests a connection to algorithms and optimization, which are central topics in computer science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.GT (Game Theory), which are all relevant to the study of optimization problems.
